The paper deals with 3D object detection from RGB-D data, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method involves semi-supervised learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of reprojection loss and box prior loss, which are common techniques in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
